						               													<description>Third Grand Battles supplement has now been released! You can build British, Spanish, Portuguese, KGL, Hanoverian, Brunswick, Nassau, Netherlands and Emigre armies using Wellington's Armies Parade Handbooks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The army list building options are very flexible and clearly laid out. Using these lists you can pretty much build any Revolutionary, Peninsular and 1815 historical army organisation using any of these nine nations. Perhaps you are looking to build a 1st Coalition Iberian army composed of Portuguese and Spanish to fight those dastardly French Revolutionaries during the War of Rousillon or maybe mix in some British and Emigre's for a Toulon campaign. Alternatively, a British expeditionary force to Egypt, a British, Spanish or Portuguese force in the peninsular or a glorious British-Allied army to drive back Napoleon from the ridges at Waterloo. Whatever you decide it can be done with this book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Such a glorious celebration of Wellington's overwhelming influence upon the wars and national armies he commanded, besides his own British redcoats, would not be complete without a few national general options such as Wellington, Moore, Crawford, Forbes, Prince of Orange and the Duke of Brunswick to name a few. Oh and to round the whole book off what better way to celebrate Wellington's Armies than a recipe for Beef Wellington to be made for your next Waterloo game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
